Privacy Policy for CPU Miner
Last updated: 10/11/2024

Welcome to CPU Miner. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use our app.

1. Information We Collect
a. Automatically Collected Information
When you use CPU Miner, we may automatically collect certain information, including but not limited to:

Device Information: Your mobile device's unique ID, model, manufacturer, and operating system.
Usage Data: Data about how you interact with the game, including gameplay, levels completed, in-game purchases, and other actions.
Log Data: IP address, browser type, Internet Service Provider, and timestamps related to your usage of our game.
b. Information from Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services like Google Analytics, Unity Ads, and Google Play Services that may collect information used to identify you.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect in the following ways:

To provide and maintain the app.
To improve gameplay and user experience.
To analyze usage patterns to enhance game features.
To serve personalized advertisements and promotions.
To process in-app purchases and manage billing.
3. Third-Party Services
We may share your data with third-party service providers to perform services on our behalf, such as:

Advertising: Unity Ads, Google AdMob
Analytics: Google Analytics for Firebase
Monetization: Google Play Billing Library for in-app purchases
These third-party services may collect information sent by your device as part of their service.

4. Data Security
We are committed to protecting your data. We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. However, please note that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

5. Children's Privacy
Our game is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we discover that we have collected information from a child under 13, we will delete such information immediately.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. Changes are effective when they are posted on this page.

7. Your Consent
By using CPU Miner, you consent to our Privacy Policy.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: theo.morris@mds.ac.nz
